				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Our Hero, who&#8217;s in need of a bit of cash, goes down to the &#8220;tracks&#8221; to make a bet. He has a tip (his sure thing, I suppose), and puts money on a person who&#8217;s forced to run around the track.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m amused: what came to mind for me with the topic was also racing of sorts ðŸ˜›</p>
<p>Nice piece. I enjoyed the description of Thomas watching the game (with his tight grip) and then, as a sign of respect, watching their slaughter as well. Both say something about the character, and one is distinctly macabre <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </p>
<p>The whole story left me wondering what the rest of the world is like.</p>
